      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAKE YOUR STAND (2) turned in a plain run last time when eighth at Gunnedah over 431m behind Scootin' Scooby (25.67) in a Grade 4/5. Was in the money the start prior. Has performed well from this box with a win and four minor placings to his name from 10 starts. Rates on top in this line up. HOW HIGH SPIKE (1) missed the frame and was safely held latest finishing 6th at this track following on from a third place finish (23.57) there the start prior. Has a good record here at this journey. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Has ability and a bold showing is expected. SUDDEN SURPRISE (7) broke from the inside draw and filled a minor placing last start, beaten only one length (19.88) behind Private Jake at Gunnedah. Can feature again. FULL TILT TOM (8) should be thereabouts despite an unplaced run here most recently.",
